article.description: — Phillip Russell's 21 points helped Southeast Missouri State defeat Boston University 63-52 on Saturday.
article.headline: Russell scores 21 as SE Missouri St. knocks off Boston U
article.linkText: Russell scores 21 as SE Missouri St. knocks off Boston U
article.story: MILWAUKEE -- — Phillip Russell's 21 points helped Southeast Missouri State defeat Boston University 63-52 on Saturday. Russell also added six rebounds for the Redhawks (5-1). Chris Harris scored 12 points and added seven rebounds. The Terriers (4-2) were led in scoring by Jonas Harper, who finished with 15 points. Nevin Zink added 10 points and seven rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
